# Pasale Backend REST API Documentation

## API Overview

- Base URL: /api
- Auth scheme: JWT Bearer token for protected endpoints
- Auth header format: Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
- Content type: application/json

## Authentication Endpoints

### 1) Signup

#### Endpoint

/api/signup/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

No

#### Request Body

| Field         | Type   | Required | Notes                                         |
| ------------- | ------ | -------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| username      | string | Yes      | Must be unique unless reusing same email flow |
| email         | string | Yes      | Lowercased by server                          |
| password      | string | Yes      | Plain text in request                         |
| phone_no      | string | No       | Saved to business profile                     |
| business_name | string | No       | Business name for created/updated business    |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                                             |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| 201    | {"message": "User created successfully. Please verify the OTP sent to your email."}  |
| 400    | {"error": "Username, email and password are required."}                              |
| 400    | {"error": "User with this email already exists."}                                    |
| 400    | {"error": "Username is already taken."}                                              |
| 400    | {"error": "Username or email already exists."}                                       |
| 503    | {"error": "Account created, but OTP delivery failed. Please try again in a moment."} |

### 2) Verify Signup OTP

#### Endpoint

/api/verify-signup-otp/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

No

#### Request Body

| Field | Type   | Required | Notes                   |
| ----- | ------ | -------- | ----------------------- |
| email | string | Yes      | Must match signup email |
| otp   | string | Yes      | 6-digit OTP             |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                         |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------ |
| 200    | {"message": "Signup OTP verified successfully!"} |
| 400    | {"error": "No OTP found"}                        |
| 400    | {"error": "OTP expired"}                         |
| 400    | {"error": "Invalid OTP"}                         |
| 404    | {"error": "User not found"}                      |
| 404    | {"error": "Business not found for this user"}    |

### 3) Login

#### Endpoint

/api/login/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

No

#### Request Body

| Field    | Type   | Required | Notes                  |
| -------- | ------ | -------- | ---------------------- |
| email    | string | Yes      | Existing user email    |
| password | string | Yes      | Existing user password |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                                       |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| 200    | {"message": "Login successful", "tokens": {"refresh": "...", "access": "..."}} |
| 401    | {"error": "Invalid credentials"}                                               |
| 404    | {"error": "User not found"}                                                    |

### 4) Refresh Access Token

#### Endpoint

/api/token/refresh/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

No

#### Request Body

| Field   | Type   | Required | Notes             |
| ------- | ------ | -------- | ----------------- |
| refresh | string | Yes      | JWT refresh token |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                         |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------ |
| 200    | {"access": "..."}                                |
| 401    | Invalid or expired token response from SimpleJWT |

