## Scheduler Endpoints

### 29) Run Staff Scheduler

#### Endpoint

/api/scheduler/b{business_id}/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

No (current code uses AllowAny)

#### Request Body

| Field              | Type      | Required | Notes                     |
| ------------------ | --------- | -------- | ------------------------- |
| business_id        | integer   | Yes      | Must be valid business id |
| shift_ids          | integer[] | Yes      | Existing shift ids        |
| max_hours_per_week | integer   | No       | Default 40                |
| apply_schedule     | boolean   | No       | Default false             |
| weights            | object    | No       | Float weights map         |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                                                            |
| ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 200    | {"status": "success", "scheduling_result": {...}, "schedule_summary": {...}, "applied": true/false} |
| 400    | Serializer errors or {"error": "No valid shifts found"}                                             |
| 404    | {"error": "Business not found"}                                                                     |
| 500    | {"error": "..."}                                                                                    |

### 30) Get Scheduled Shifts

#### Endpoint

/api/scheduler/b{business_id}/

#### Method

GET

#### Auth

Effectively Yes in implementation (request.user ownership check), but class permission is AllowAny

#### Request Body

None

#### Query Parameters

| Param       | Required | Notes                          |
| ----------- | -------- | ------------------------------ |
| employee_id | No       | Filter by assigned employee id |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                             |
| ------ | ------------------------------------ |
| 200    | {"status": "success", "data": [...]} |
| 400    | {"error": "business_id is required"} |
| 403    | {"error": "Permission denied"}       |
| 500    | {"error": "..."}                     |

## Order Endpoints

### 31) List Orders / Get Order

#### Endpoint

/api/orders/b{business_id}/

#### Method

GET

#### Auth

No (current code uses AllowAny)

#### Request Body

None

#### Query Parameters

| Param    | Required | Notes                                                                                                    |
| -------- | -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| order_id | No       | Not wired in URL for this route; to fetch one order use route with c{value} pattern and service behavior |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                        |
| ------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| 200    | Array of order objects                          |
| 400    | {"error": "Business ID is required in the url"} |
| 500    | {"error": "..."}                                |

### 32) Create Order

#### Endpoint

/api/orders/b{business_id}/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

No (current code uses AllowAny)

#### Request Body

| Field        | Type    | Required    | Notes                                                    |
| ------------ | ------- | ----------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| total_amount | number  | Yes         | Required                                                 |
| tax          | number  | No          | Default 0                                                |
| discount     | number  | No          | Default 0                                                |
| customer_id  | integer | Conditional | Required if counter_id not provided                      |
| counter_id   | integer | Conditional | Required if customer_id not provided                     |
| items        | array   | Conditional | Required when creating counter order without customer_id |

Item object fields:

| Field      | Type    | Required | Notes                    |
| ---------- | ------- | -------- | ------------------------ |
| product_id | integer | Yes      | Must exist               |
| quantity   | integer | Yes      | Must be positive integer |
| status_id  | integer | No       | OrderItemStatus id       |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                                                                      |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 201    | {"message": "Order created successfully.", "order": {...}, "counter_id": ..., "items_created": n}             |
| 400    | Missing required fields, invalid numeric values, invalid product/status, invalid customer/counter combination |
| 404    | {"error": "Business does not exist."} or customer/counter not found                                           |
| 500    | {"error": "C0INSERR: ..."}                                                                                    |

### 33) Create Order via c{value} Route

#### Endpoint

/api/orders/b{business_id}/c{value}/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

No (current code uses AllowAny)

#### Request Body

Same as Create Order.

#### Notes

- Due to two identical URL patterns in router, this route binds to customer_id parameter in current Django resolution order.
- The counter-specific route with same path shape is effectively unreachable.

#### Responses

Same as Create Order.

### 34) Update Order

#### Endpoint

No direct URL currently maps order_id into OrderView.put in api.urls.

#### Method

PUT

#### Auth

No (current code uses AllowAny)

#### Request Body

Partial order fields.

#### Notes

Method exists but router currently does not provide an order_id path parameter, so this operation is not reachable through configured URLs.

### 35) Delete Order

#### Endpoint

No direct URL currently maps order_id into OrderView.delete in api.urls.

#### Method

DELETE

#### Auth

No (current code uses AllowAny)

#### Request Body

None

#### Notes

Method exists but router currently does not provide an order_id path parameter, so this operation is not reachable through configured URLs.

