| Status | Response                                                        |
| ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 200    | {"business": "...", "low_stock_count": n, "suggestions": [...]} |
| 200    | {"message": "No low stock items found.", "suggestions": []}     |
| 400    | {"error": "Business ID is required"} or Apriori error           |
| 404    | {"error": "No business found for this user"}                    |

### 41) Get Stock Alerts

#### Endpoint

/api/inventory/alerts/b{business_id}/

#### Method

GET

#### Auth

Yes

#### Request Body

None

#### Query Parameters

| Param    | Required | Notes                        |
| -------- | -------- | ---------------------------- |
| resolved | No       | true or false, default false |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                    |
| ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| 200    | {"business": "...", "total_alerts": n, "showing": "resolved | unresolved", "alerts": [...]} |
| 400    | {"error": "Business ID is required"}                        |
| 404    | {"error": "No business found for this user"}                |

### 42) Resolve Stock Alert

#### Endpoint

/api/inventory/alerts/b{business_id}/{alert_id}/resolve/

#### Method

PUT

#### Auth

Yes

#### Request Body

None

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                                                                  |
| ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 200    | {"message": "Alert #<id> resolved successfully", "alert_id": <id>, "product": "...", "is_resolved": true} |
| 400    | {"error": "Business ID is required"}                                                                      |
| 404    | {"error": "No business found for this user"}                                                              |
| 404    | {"error": "Alert #<id> not found"}                                                                        |

### 43) Retrain Apriori Model

#### Endpoint

/api/inventory/retrain/b{business_id}/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

Yes

#### Request Body

None

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                                                                                                                                   |
| ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 200    | {"message": "Retrain completed successfully", "business": "...", "rules_found": "...", "rules_saved": n, "old_rules_deleted": n, "alerts_created": n, "alerts_skipped": n} |
| 400    | {"error": "Business ID is required"} or retrain error                                                                                                                      |
| 404    | {"error": "No business found for this user"}                                                                                                                               |

## Cart Endpoints

These routes are mounted at project URL level and still use /api prefix.

### 44) Get Cart Items (Customer Scope)

#### Endpoint

/api/cart/business/{business_id}/customer/{customer_id}/

#### Method

GET

#### Auth

Yes

#### Request Body

None

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                        |
| ------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| 200    | Array of cart item objects                      |
| 400    | {"error": "Business ID is required in the url"} |
| 400    | {"error": "Customer ID is required in the url"} |
| 404    | {"error": "Customer does not exist"}            |
| 500    | {"error": "..."}                                |

### 45) Add Items To Cart (Customer Scope)

#### Endpoint

/api/cart/business/{business_id}/customer/{customer_id}/

#### Method

POST

#### Auth

Yes

#### Request Body

Array of item objects.

| Field      | Type    | Required | Notes                                                  |
| ---------- | ------- | -------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| unit_price | number  | Yes      | Required per item                                      |
| quantity   | number  | Yes      | Required per item                                      |
| Product_id | integer | Yes      | Product id key is Product_id in current implementation |

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                                     |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------ |
| 201    | {"message": "Items added to cart successfully", "data": ...} |
| 400    | {"error": "Invalid data format. Expected a list of items."}  |
| 400    | Missing required per-item field error                        |
| 404    | {"error": "Customer does not exist"}                         |
| 404    | {"error": "Product with ID <id> does not exist."}            |
| 500    | {"error": "..."}                                             |

### 46) Cart Routes with Incomplete URL Parameters

#### Endpoint

/api/cart/

#### Method

GET, POST

#### Auth

Yes

#### Request Body

Depends on method.

#### Responses

| Status | Response                                        |
| ------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| 400    | {"error": "Business ID is required in the url"} |

#### Notes

This route is mapped but view logic requires business_id and customer_id, so it always returns validation errors.

### 47) Delete Cart Item

#### Endpoint

No URL currently provides cart_id to OrderCartView.delete.

#### Method

DELETE

#### Auth

Yes

#### Request Body

None

#### Notes

Delete method exists but configured URLs do not pass cart_id, so this operation is currently unreachable.

## Operational Notes

### Celery Worker

- Command: celery -A backend worker --loglevel=info --pool=solo

### Runtime Requirements

- Install dependencies from requirements.txt
- Redis-compatible broker required for Celery task queue (for example Memurai on Windows)

## Important Current Router/Permission Caveats

- Several write endpoints are marked AllowAny in code, even where business logic assumes authenticated users.
- Order routes include two identical c{int} patterns, so only the first one resolves in Django.
- Some view methods exist for update/delete but do not have matching URL patterns with required path parameters.
